Title: Funky Fanfare

Based on my research, the best entrances fall into three camps: 
1. songs referencing your work 
2. wrestler intro vibes 
3. jams to dance your way in

Hard to reference my work anonymously, and we've already done wrestler entrance, so I'm leaning into a song that'll have me and the host dancing in
 
It's also key that the instrumental holds up; the house band likely won't do vocals. 
So here's a jam famously sampled in Old School Rules by DOOM. I listened to that album endlessly in high school.

Title: Musette And Drums
Comment: A musette is a type of French bagpipe with a soft sound (obvs). Literal/metaphorical is a tough distinction here, but it seems about as literal as you're going to get from Liz Fraser - she states the title plainly in the lyrics, plus I'm guessing that the slightly droney synth you can hear is a nod to the musette. (The "drums" are a nod to the "drums"). Also this song is a good rejoinder to anyone calling Cocteau Twins "Dream Pop" at this point in their career - holy shit does this song go hard.

Title: Flight

My future sister-in-law is dating a guy in this band. I don't think he knows that we know he's in a band. He's in our "friends" Music League and I've always wanted to submit one of their songs and play dumb.

Anyway, if this song doesn't do well, then David can't join the family. I'm drawing a line in the sand.

Title: Sometimes
Comment: Jimmy Gnecco is a longtime friend of a few of my friends and weâ€™ve all hung out a lot over the years. So dramatic on stage but a very nice, quiet, unassuming guy socially. My favorite memory is the time he came over exhausted and jetlagged after a tour. We were all playing Cards Against Humanity when he just folded his arms on the table and put his head down and went to sleep, so we kept trying to laugh quietly and let him rest. Wholesome times with musicians! Anyway this is their biggest hit.
